sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
Attaches the specified storage volume to the specified instance.

Inputs :

  • Instance ID - OCID of the instance.
  • Compartment ID - OCID of the compartment.
  • Volume ID - OCID of the volume.
  • Type - The type of volume. The only supported values are "ISCSI" and "Paravirtualized".
  • Display Name - Name of the volume attachment.
  • Is Read Only - Whether the attachment was created in read-only mode.
  • Is Shareable - Whether the attachment should be created in shareable mode. If an attachment is created in shareable mode, then other instances can attach the same volume.

Outputs :

  • Status - If the request is executed successfully, Status is set to "Success". If there is a failure, Status is set to "Error".
  • Error Message - Reason for error, along with code. Populated only when an error occurs.
  • Volume Attachment ID - OCID of the volume attachment.
  • Availability Domain - The availability domain of an instance.
  • Compartment ID - OCID of the compartment.
  • Instance ID - OCID of the instance.
  • Display Name - Name of the volume attachment.
  • Time Created - Date and time at which the volume attachment was created.
  • Lifecycle State - Current state of the volume attachment.
  • Volume ID - OCID of the volume.
  • Attachment Type - Type of volume attachment.
  • Is Read Only - Whether the attachment was created in read-only mode.
  • Is Shareable - Whether the attachment should be created in shareable mode.

Error Messages :

  • Bad Request.
  • Unauthorized.
  • Not Found.
  • Internal Server Error.

To use this action, the corresponding Oracle connection and credential must be created and associated with the Oracle Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.
sys_hub_action_type_definition.name: Attach Volume
